---

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1} into small pieces. Heat a drizzle
of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and onion to the pan and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Add the garlic and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder) to the chicken and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans, @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and
@Water for the Sauce{75%ml} until well combined.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Smoky Base Paste{1%sachet},
@Honey{1%tbsp} and @Butter{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little too thick.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the smoky chicken and beans.

Finish by drizzling over the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Enjoy!